The paper deals with the generation of random variates, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of an oracle and quadtree-style extension suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses lower bounds and optimality, which are common themes in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
